      "Agriculture has always been applied phenology: planting calendars, chill-hour requirements for fruit trees, growing degree-day models for crop stages and insect generations, harvest windows. Climate trends force updates to those calendars — earlier blooms risk frost; altered pest voltinism changes management.",
      "Migration phenology couples hemispheres. Radar ornithology, geolocators, and satellite tags reveal departure and arrival timing; stopover quality determines whether schedules can flex. Marine phenology — plankton blooms, fish spawning — underpins fisheries recruitment.",
